<item>
            <title>[PIG-5366] Enable PigStreamingDepend to load from current directory in newer Perl versions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-5366</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A perl&#160;related issue found while testing streaming. In newer perl versions (&amp;gt;5.26), current directory (&quot;.&quot;) is not included in @INC, so PerlStreamingDepend may fail during &quot;use PigStreamingModule;&quot;. A possible solution is to let this module add current directory for itself to make it more independent from the environment (current perl version).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test case was:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
define CMD `perl PigStreamingDepend.pl - sio_5_1 sio_5_2` input(stdin) output(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;sio_5_1&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;sio_5_2&apos;&lt;/span&gt;) ship(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;./libexec/PigStreamingDepend.pl&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;./libexec/PigStreamingModule.pm&apos;&lt;/span&gt;);
A = load &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;/user/hrt_qa/tests/data/singlefile/studenttab10k&apos;&lt;/span&gt;;
B = stream A through CMD;
store B into &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;/user/hrt_qa/out/hrtqa-1539851229-streaming.conf-StreamingIO/StreamingIO_5.out&apos;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
